Author: CoinKing88#1540
Content: I pay 0,35% but thats calculated over the assetsvalue invested. Luring ppl in that think "if i lose at least i don't pay fee" is a clear red flag for me. Besides that, crypto is not mature enough for me to invest a serious % of my liquid assets and i think that goes for almost all of the ppl they are targeting with this easy-entry-into-crypto-product. If you really think that you can work miracles you would ask for a flat fee, even when you have a loss year (b/c you have put the same amount of effort into it, maybe even more trying to get into the black). So fee only on profits screams scam to me. TLDR: Scam.

Author: allbits#5898
Content:
Look at coinmarketcap and see how many markets there are for doge and how many for kmd. It's 312 vs 24

Then consider that, at the present time, the by far predominant use cases for crypto are permissionless store of value, speculation, and transferring value to and from and between centralized exchanges. Doge has a far, far bigger network as far as that's concerned and so, while these remain the predominant use cases, how is it surprising that doge and ltc etc have higher market caps? Blaming it on others stupidity is not correct in my opinion.
